Calendar Effects: WESM Price of GBPC Plants¶

Analysis on whether the spot market price movement of GBPC plants is related to the calendar, such as the day of the week, time of the month, time of the year.

Initial Findings:

  1. Data
    • RTD Market Prices & Schedules from 2015 to 2019 of CEDC, PEDC and TPC
    • Incomplete/Missing data removed
    • Downloaded from GETAPP
  2. Distribution
    • Raw data is narrowly distributed as affected by large values from pricing error runs
    • We clip the prices from 0 to 15k to get better distribution
    • Mean price of 2.5
  3. Calendar Effects
    • Aggregation is estimated using averaging with 95% CI
    • CEDC U1, U2, U3 share similar price profile
    • TPC U1 and U2 also share similar profile despite different capacities.
    • PEDC U3 price profile is different from PEDC U1 and U2.
    • By Year
      • Prices dipped in 2016; Has been increasing ever since
    • By Month
      • Prices peak in June during summer
      • However, there is secondary peak in Oct
    • By Weekday
      • Weekday prices are high on Tues and Friday, low on Thursday
      • Prices dip on weekends
    • By Hour
      • Three price peaks occur during the day.
      • Morning peak at 10-11AM, then dipping during midday
      • Second peak at 2-3pm. Evening peak at 7-8pm.
      • However, the max peak is different in Cebu and Panay
      • Max peak for CEDC/TPC during afternoon while Panay max peak on evenings

To Do:

  1. Recover missing data
  2. Other factors affecting the prices
  3. Run initial forecasts

Add 'Year', 'Month', 'Day', Weekend, Weekday column for visualization¶

In [ ]:
year = df_gbpc['Datetime'].dt.year
month = df_gbpc['Datetime'].dt.month_name().str.slice(stop=3)
dayofweek = df_gbpc['Datetime'].dt.day_name().str.slice(stop=3)
day = df_gbpc['Datetime'].dt.day

months = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']

weekdays= ['Mon', 'Tue', 'Wed', 'Thu', 'Fri', 'Sat', 'Sun']

df_gbpc = df_gbpc.assign(Year=year, Month=month, Dayofweek=dayofweek, Day=day)

df_gbpc['Month'] = pd.Categorical(df_gbpc['Month'], categories=months, ordered=True)

df_gbpc['Dayofweek'] = pd.Categorical(df_gbpc['Dayofweek'], categories=weekdays, ordered=True)
